ZZ ROCKS VIII</strong></em> at <strong>Red Rocks Amphitheatre</strong> in=
 <strong>Morrison=2C CO</strong> on<strong> October 3=2C 2026</strong>. Su=
pported by <strong>Frost Children</strong>=2C <strong>KAVARI</strong>=2C<s=
trong> Izzy Camina</strong>=2C and <strong>Sakr</strong>=2C this year=E2=
=80=99s <em>REZZ ROCKS</em> will be a one-night only experience.<br>
<br>
Since its inception=2C <em>REZZ ROCKS</em> has evolved into one of the mos=
t anticipated headline events at the legendary Colorado venue=2C serving a=
s a platform for REZZ to fully explore the outer edges of her sound=2C vis=
uals=2C and conceptual world-building. Red Rocks has been home to some of=
 REZZ's greatest career milestones=2C from becoming the venue's first elec=
tronic female headliner in 2018 to hosting its first all-female lineup in=
 2024. Each year=2C <em>REZZ ROCKS</em> offers a unique chapter in her art=
istic evolution=2C with production=2C set design=2C and musical direction=
 crafted exclusively for Red Rocks=E2=80=99 natural amphitheater. <em>REZZ=
 ROCKS VIII </em>continues this tradition=2C solidifying the event as a de=
fining moment on REZZ=E2=80=99s annual calendar.<br>
<br>
Last year=E2=80=99s<em> REZZ ROCKS VII</em> was a two-night whirlwind spec=
tacle=2C with Night 1 featuring a surprise <em>PORTAL </em>set and Night 2=
 marking the return of REZZs <em><a href=3D"https://COM.us19.list-manage.c=
om/track/click?u=3Ddcc6afc55b72ac85d6555d821&id=3D41a94b3e0c&e=3D929a9ba3f9" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size=
